dead yet. And two new feature detects are in this release, one for the focus-within pseudo-selector and one for variable fonts.</p>
<p>Happy developing in 2018!</p>
<p><strong>New Feature Detect(s)</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/oliverjash">@oliverjash</a> added test for CSS <code>:focus-within</code> pseudo-selector <a href="https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr/pull/2287">#2287</a></li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/patrickkettner">@patrickkettner</a> added test for variable fonts <a href="https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr/pull/2202">#2202</a></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Fixes</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Contributions by @cliener, @jayeb, @bholley, @rejas, @simongareste, @timkraut, @philippsimon, @patrickhlauke, @luftywiranda13, @milesthedisch, @strarsis
which all provided <a href="https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr/compare/v3.5.0...v3.6.0">fixes</a> for this release</li>
</ul>
]]></description><link>https://modernizr.com/news//news/modernizr-3-6-0</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://modernizr.com/news//news/modernizr-3-6-0</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[<a href="https://github.com/rejas/">Rejas</a>]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 04 Mar 2018 23:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Modernizr 3.5.0]]></title><description><![CDATA[<p>Instead of quietly updating the library like we did for our 3.4.0 release (yes, that happened ‚Äî <a href="https://modernizr.com/news/modernizr-3-4-0">see the full changelog here</a>), we have an exciting new feature detect as part of 3.5.0: CSS Grids!</p>
<p>With browsers <a href="http://caniuse.com/#feat=css-grid">adding support for CSS Grids in their latest releases</a>, the time to <a href="https://alistapart.com/article/practical-grid">start using CSS Grids</a> is truly here. Just one caveat: IE11 and current shipping versions of Edge do not support the new syntax, but <em>do</em> support the old legacy CSS Grids proposal‚Äîand only one of them supports, uh, <code>@supports</code>.</p>
<p>So in <strong>3.5.0</strong> we‚Äôre adding two tests in one: the now-standard official CSS Grid syntax as <code>Modernizr.cssgrid</code>, and the old proposal‚Äôs syntax as <code>Modernizr.cssgridlegacy</code>. There is also an additional polyfill available for the Pointer Events test, named PEP. Lastly, dependencies were updated.</p>
<p>Happy developing!</p>
<p><strong>New Feature Detect(s)</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/kurafire">@kurafire</a> added CSS Grid test for old &amp; new syntaxes <a href="https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr/pull/2189">#2189</a></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Updated</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/roblarsen">@roblarsen</a> + <a href="https://github.com/patrickkettner">@patrickkettner</a> added PEP to pointer events as a polyfill <a href="https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr/pull/2179">#2179</a></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Updated Dependencies</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Update grunt-contrib-clean to version 1.1.0 üöÄ <a href="https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr/pull/2188">#2188</a></li>
<li>Update yargs to version 7.0.2 üöÄ <a href="https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr/pull/2175">#2175</a></li>
</ul>
